{"key":"processedPost-20099290","value":{"id":20099290,"first":20098878,"last":20102482,"when":1402231630,"utime":"06/08/14 03:47 PM","content":"<img style=\"max-width:192px;height:auto;\" src=\"https://files.shroomery.org/smileys/facepalm.gif\" alt=\":facepalm:\" title=\":facepalm:\"/><br /><br />Thicker filters have <b>LESS</b> resistance than thinner ones.&nbsp; I've typed that at least 1000 times over the years and it's on every spec sheet.<br /><br />Choose a filter with sufficient resistance to achieve laminar flow.<br /><br />Most flowhood filters are 5\" to 7\" in thickness.&nbsp; They have high resistance, but less debris holding capacity.&nbsp; This is why we use prefilters.<br /><br />Clean room filters (not what you want) are thicker at 12\" to 15\" so they have more debris holding capacity, but a lower resistance to provide higher flow rates to clean entire rooms.&nbsp; These are not recommended for flow hoods.<br />RR","title":"Re: HEPA Filter for Flow Hood"}}